<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-464] MongoDbUtils incorrectly synchronizes DB instances if more than one DB is accessed</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-464</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Calling &lt;tt&gt;SimpleMongoDbFactory.getDb(name)&lt;/tt&gt; returns same DB instance in a transaction where multiple mongo databases are involved.&lt;br/&gt;
That&apos;s because &lt;tt&gt;MongoDbUtils.doGetDB&lt;/tt&gt; retrieves always the default database from &lt;tt&gt;DbHolder&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
